COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 46, L.D. 29
1 Amend the resolve by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or
2 section number to read consecutively.
3 SUMMARY
44 This amendment, which is the majority report of the committee, adds a provision to the
55 bill directing the Department of Transportation, subject to available funding resources,
66 permitting and municipal agreements, to remove state-owned inactive existing railroad
77 track along the section known as the Calais Branch from the Route 214 intersection in
88 Ayers Junction in the Town of Pembroke to Route 1 in the City of Calais and to replace the
99 track with an interim multi-use trail on the existing rail bed.
